  "text": "also the accompanying video). Although our method does not result in optimal trajectories, most of the particles achieved the expected interpolated goal location while avoiding the interpolated obstacle. Linear Bellman combination [CITATION_1] ] results in an optimal behavior, but yields two different targets and obstacles. We performed numerical comparison with the simulated reference (Fig.  12) . For each particle, we integrate the contribution of the reference value function along its path. As the reference particles maximize this criterion, this provides a numerical reference score to which we can compare. As can be seen in Fig.12 , linear interpolation fails at obtaining a good score at intermediate times since particles trajectory significantly diverge from the expected paths.",
